# Ignore uncompressed CPython libraries.
# Only the .gz files are committed to git — include_bytes!() reads
# the .gz at compile time and decompresses at runtime.
#
# BUILD INSTRUCTIONS (adding a new platform):
#   1. Cross-compile CPython 3.12 for the target
#   2. gzip the resulting .so/.dylib/.a:
#        gzip -c libpython3.12.so > vendor/python/<target>/libpython3.12.so.gz
#   3. Commit the .gz file
#   4. Add a #[cfg(...)] block in src/python/cpython.rs
#   5. Rebuild
#
# The .gz is compiled into the binary via include_bytes!().
# No runtime download needed in production.
*.dylib
*.so
*.a
